<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{7}{y}=-{35}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{9}{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({6},{1}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{7}{y}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}=-{35}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{35}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{\left(\frac{{-{35}-{\left({7}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{7}}}}\right)}+{9}{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{2}}{{-{{7}}}}\cdot{\left(-{35}\right)}--\frac{{2}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left({7}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10}-{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{3}--{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2}+{\left({9}\right)}\right)}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{7}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={1}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{7}{\left({1}\right)}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{\left({7}\right)}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}=-{35}-{\left({7}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{42}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({6},{1}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

